01:04.212 --> 01:06.313
She's home, but she's not staying

01:06.347 --> 01:08.515
unless Dad agrees to go to counseling.

01:08.549 --> 01:10.183
Well, that sounds reasonable.

01:10.218 --> 01:13.520
Are you kidding? Mr.
Juergens in a shrink's office?

01:13.554 --> 01:15.422
That's not happening, is it, Amy?

01:15.456 --> 01:17.858
I thought maybe it was until you said that.

01:18.893 --> 01:22.129
So, um, did he call you? Jimmy?

01:22.163 --> 01:25.165
No, but we agreed we're not going
to call each other every day.

01:25.199 --> 01:26.700
We're two hours apart,

01:26.734 --> 01:29.169
and you know how lon
g-distance relationships are.

01:29.203 --> 01:30.303
They just don't work.

01:31.372 --> 01:32.606
So he hasn't called?

01:32.640 --> 01:33.773
Has Jesse called you?

01:33.808 --> 01:38.178
Oh, yeah. Every two hours.

01:38.212 --> 01:40.514
Jack calls me.
You know, not every two hours,

01:40.548 --> 01:43.183
but every day.

01:43.217 --> 01:45.352
But we're not in a lon
g-distance relationship.

01:45.386 --> 01:47.254
Are you in a relationship?

01:47.288 --> 01:48.855
You know what they're doing.

01:48.890 --> 01:50.991
So yes. Madison.

01:51.025 --> 01:52.859
Look, it's not that bad.

01:52.894 --> 01:55.529
I like it for now.

01:55.563 --> 01:57.497
Are you doing anything with Jimmy?

01:57.532 --> 01:59.199
No, not really.

01:59.233 --> 02:01.368
We did make out for a couple of hours.

02:01.402 --> 02:04.471
And he didn't call you? Okay, that's weird.

02:04.505 --> 02:05.872
Is he a bad kisser?

02:05.907 --> 02:07.040
No.

02:07.074 --> 02:09.142
Uh-oh.

02:09.176 --> 02:10.243
What?

02:10.277 --> 02:11.978
Nothing. Madison...

02:12.013 --> 02:13.813
I am not a bad kisser.

02:13.848 --> 02:16.750
If I were a bad kisser,
we wouldn't have made out for two hours.

02:16.784 --> 02:18.518
Maybe he was trying to teach you something.

02:18.553 --> 02:19.653
Did he seem bored?

02:19.687 --> 02:21.655
No.

02:26.527 --> 02:27.827
I can't believe he didn't call her.

02:27.862 --> 02:29.362
Something's wrong.

02:30.364 --> 02:31.998
Hey, girlfriend. Did he call?

02:32.033 --> 02:33.833
No, he did not call.

02:33.868 --> 02:35.302
He does not have to call me.

02:35.336 --> 02:37.170
He can call me if he feels like calling me.

02:37.205 --> 02:39.839
Yeah, that's right. Or you can
call him if you feel like calling--

02:39.874 --> 02:41.508
I don't feel like calling him.

02:41.542 --> 02:43.510
Oh, right. There's a lot
going on at your house.

02:43.544 --> 02:44.544
Goodbye, Adrian.

02:46.214 --> 02:47.581
Oh, hey. Good morning.

02:47.615 --> 02:49.883
Yeah, I'll see you later.

02:49.917 --> 02:52.185
Wait, did you ask them?

02:52.220 --> 02:54.521
Did you ask your parents to
come over and meet my parents?

02:54.555 --> 02:57.190
They can do it any time.
Well, any time my mom's not working.

02:57.225 --> 02:59.025
No, I didn't get a chance.

02:59.060 --> 03:00.427
Oh, come on. Please?

03:00.461 --> 03:01.962
Adrian, my mom does not like the fact

03:01.996 --> 03:04.564
that I moved out of the house
and you and I are having sex.

03:04.599 --> 03:05.832
That doesn't mean they won't like me.

03:05.866 --> 03:07.033
Yes, it does.

03:07.068 --> 03:09.703
Look, my parents want to meet your parents.

03:09.737 --> 03:11.805
